   "source": [
    "# Malignant Comments Classifier Project."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03358b6e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Problem Statement:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0387ef0f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The proliferation of social media enables people to express their opinions widely online. However, at the same time, this has resulted in the emergence of conflict and hate, making online environments uninviting for users. Although researchers have found that hate is a problem across multiple platforms, there is a lack of models for online hate detection.\n",
    "\n",
    "Online hate, described as abusive language, aggression, cyberbullying, hatefulness and many others has been identified as a major threat on online social media platforms. Social media platforms are the most prominent grounds for such toxic behaviour.   \n",
    "\n",
    "There has been a remarkable increase in the cases of cyberbullying and trolls on various social media platforms. Many celebrities and influences are facing backlashes from people and have to come across hateful and offensive comments. This can take a toll on anyone and affect them mentally leading to depression, mental illness, self-hatred and suicidal thoughts.    \n",
    "\n",
    "Internet comments are bastions of hatred and vitriol. While online anonymity has provided a new outlet for aggression and hate speech, machine learning can be used to fight it. The problem we sought to solve was the tagging of internet comments that are aggressive towards other users. This means that insults to third parties such as celebrities will be tagged as unoffensive, but “u are an idiot” is clearly offensive.\n",
    "\n",
    "Our goal is to build a prototype of online hate and abuse comment classifier which can used to classify hate and offensive comments so that it can be controlled and restricted from spreading hatred and cyberbullying.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a01286f3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The train dataset is comprised of both dependent variable (target) and independent variables. In train dataset the label can be either 0 or 1, where 0 denotes a NO while 1 denotes a YES. There are various comments which have multiple labels. The first attribute is a unique ID associated with each comment. Since the target variable is consists of 2 classes 0 and 1 which can be termed as categorical in nature which makes this to be a \"**Classification Problem**\".\n",
    "\n",
    "The test dataset contains only independent variables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b32344fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Feature Information:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cceca0d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Malignant: It is the Label column, which includes values 0 and 1, denoting if the comment is malignant or not.\n",
    "- Highly Malignant: It denotes comments that are highly malignant and hurtful.\n",
    "- Rude: It denotes comments that are very rude and offensive.\n",
    "- Threat: It contains indication of the comments that are giving any threat to someone.\n",
    "- Abuse: It is for comments that are abusive in nature.\n",
    "- Loathe: It describes the comments which are hateful and loathing in nature.\n",
    "- ID: It includes unique Ids associated with each comment text given.\n",
    "- Comment text: This column contains the comments extracted from various social media platforms."
   ]
  },

    "# Text Processing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "6a7ba6fe",

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Importing Required libraries\n",
    "import nltk\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import string\n",
    "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
    "from wordcloud import WordCloud\n",
    "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
    "from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "id": "61be9c99",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Replacing '\\n' in comment_text\n",
    "train_mc['comment_text'] = train_mc['comment_text'].replace('\\n',' ')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "id": "f3bddab4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "</style>\n",
       "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n",
       "  <thead>\n",
       "    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n",
       "      <th></th>\n",

    "# Replacing '\\n' in comment_text\n",
    "test_mc['comment_text'] = test_mc['comment_text'].replace('\\n',' ')\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3c487319",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I have converted comments into lower case using the above coding in both train and test data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2a7dc93",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now I am going to clean the data by removing/replacing URLs, Numbers, punctuations, converting numbers to words etc. \n",
    "\n",
    "We can also observe special characters at the top of the common letter or characters if we press a longtime while typing, for example, résumé. If we are not removing these types of noise from the text, then the model will consider resume and résumé; both are two different words. So, I am replacing them as well. Also, removing extra white spaces is also important. We can not get any information from extra spaces, so that we can ignore all additional spaces such as 0ne or more newlines, tabs, extra spaces."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f7b2dc67",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Cleaning data in train dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "id": "f789a832",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Replacing email addresses with \"email\"\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^.+@[^\\.].*\\.[a-z]{2,}$','emailaddress')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing URLs with 'webaddress'\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"]=train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^https\\://[a-zA-Z0-9\\-\\.]+\\.[a-zA-Z]{2,3}(/\\S*)?$','webaddress')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing money symbols with 'moneysymb' (£ can be typed with ALT key + 156)\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'£|\\$','dollers')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing 10 digit phone numbers (formats include paranthesis, spaces, no spaces, dashes) with 'phonenumber'\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^\\(?[\\d]{3}\\)?[\\s-]?[\\d]{3}[\\s-]?[\\d]{4}$', 'phonenumber')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing numbers with 'numbr'\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'\\d+(\\.\\d+)?','numbr')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Removing punctuation\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'[^\\w\\d\\s]', ' ')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing whitespace between terms with a single space\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'\\s+', ' ')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Removing leading and trailing whitespace\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^\\s+|\\s+?$', '')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d72d5a77",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Removing Stop words"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "id": "48f6e4e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Removing stopwords from train dataset\n",
    "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english') + ['u','ü','ur','4','2','im','dont','doin','ure'])\n",
    "\n",
    "train_mc[\"comment_text\"] = train_mc[\"comment_text\"].apply(lambda x:' '.join(term for term in x.split() \n",
    "                                                                            if term not in stop_words))\n",
    "lem=WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
    "train_mc['comment_text'] = train_mc['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(lem.lemmatize(t) for t in x.split()))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "901671d9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Cleaning data in test dataset"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 49,
   "id": "5979d348",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Replacing email addresses with \"email\"\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^.+@[^\\.].*\\.[a-z]{2,}$','emailaddress')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing URLs with 'webaddress'\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^https\\://[a-zA-Z0-9\\-\\.]+\\.[a-zA-Z]{2,3}(/\\S*)?$','webaddress')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing money symbols with 'moneysymb' (£ can be typed with ALT key + 156)\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'£|\\$','dollers')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing 10 digit phone numbers (formats include paranthesis, spaces, no spaces, dashes) with 'phonenumber'\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^\\(?[\\d]{3}\\)?[\\s-]?[\\d]{3}[\\s-]?[\\d]{4}$', 'phonenumber')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing numbers with 'numbr'\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'\\d+(\\.\\d+)?','numbr')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Removing punctuation\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'[^\\w\\d\\s]', ' ')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replacing whitespace between terms with a single space\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'\\s+', ' ')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Removing leading and trailing whitespace\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].str.replace(r'^\\s+|\\s+?$', '')"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

    "#### Removing Stop words"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 50,
   "id": "996684d3",

   "source": [
    "# Removing stop words from test dataset\n",
    "stp_words = set(stopwords.words('english') + ['u','ü','ur','4','2','im','dont','doin','ure'])\n",
    "\n",
    "test_mc[\"comment_text\"] = test_mc[\"comment_text\"].apply(lambda x:' '.join(term for term in x.split() \n",
    "                                                                            if term not in stp_words))\n",
    "lemma=WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
    "test_mc['comment_text'] = test_mc['comment_text'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join(lemma.lemmatize(t) for t in x.split()))"
   ]

    "# Malignant Word Cloud\n",
    "malignants = train_mc['comment_text'][train_mc['malignant']==1]\n",
    "\n",
    "malignant_cloud = WordCloud(width=500,height=400,background_color='white',max_words=30).generate(' '.join(malignants))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6,6),facecolor='k')\n",
    "plt.imshow(malignant_cloud)\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(pad=0)\n",
    "plt.title(label = \"Words frequented in malignant\",fontdict={'fontsize':16, 'color':'white'} )\n",

    "# Balancing data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "id": "12f59973",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Importing the Oversampling library and Counter\n",
    "from imblearn.over_sampling import RandomOverSampler\n",
    "from collections import Counter"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "id": "89e6d5a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The number of classes before fit Counter({0: 100342, 1: 11357})\n",
      "The number of classes after fit Counter({0: 100342, 1: 75256})\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# We are trying to increase the points of minimum label data\n",
    "OS = RandomOverSampler(0.75)\n",
    "train_x,train_y = OS.fit_resample(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "print(\"The number of classes before fit {}\".format(Counter(y_train)))\n",
    "print(\"The number of classes after fit {}\".format(Counter(train_y)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e77f7a94",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We are using RandomOverSampler method to ensure that all the categories present in our label data have the same value. After applying oversampling we are once again listing the values of our label column to cross verify the updated information. Here we see that we have successfully resolved the class imbalance problem and now all the categories have same data ensuring that the machine learning model does not get biased towards one categor"
   ]
  },
  {

    "\n",
    "lg=LogisticRegression()\n",
    "lg.fit(train_x,train_y)\n",
    "pred_lg=lg.predict(x_test)\n",
    "\n",

    "print(\"Hamming loss: \",hamming_loss(y_test,pred_lg))\n",

      "                precision    recall  f1-score   support\n",
      "\n",

     ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "\n",
    "mnb=MultinomialNB()\n",
    "mnb.fit(train_x,train_y)\n",
    "pred_mnb=mnb.predict(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Accuracy score: \",accuracy_score(y_test,pred_mnb))\n",
    "print(\"Roc_auc_score: \",roc_auc_score(y_test,pred_mnb))\n",
    "print(\"Log loss : \",log_loss(y_test,pred_mnb))     \n",
    "print(\"Hamming loss: \",hamming_loss(y_test,pred_mnb))\n",
    "print('Confusion matrix: \\n',confusion_matrix(y_test,pred_mnb))\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4e4dac28",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the Accuracy Score and the cross validation score of the Logistic Regression Model are good and the AUC score is the highest among others we shall consider this model for hyper parameter tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "We shall use GridSearchCV for hyper parameter tuning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 120,
   "id": "988d6160",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "parameters={\n",
    "    'C': [0.2,0.3,0.4],\n",
    "    'penalty': ['l1', 'l2'],\n",
    "    'solver':['newton-cg','lbfgs'],\n",
    "    'multi_class':['auto','ovr']}\n",
    "grid_lg = GridSearchCV(lg, param_grid = parameters, cv = 4, scoring='accuracy')"
   ]
  },
